Release 2.7.007
---------------
FIXED: PostgreSQL compatiblity issues
FIXED: Spurious error message on successfull document upload when debigging output is enabled
FIXED: Login verification strictness (which previoulsy used a weaker test than the standard require_login() )
FIXED: Several minor rendering glitches
FIXED: Browser crash issue (from an infinite loop in the event system) on Moodle 3.2 after clicking the page space on some systems
CHANGED: Default values in moodle configuration parameters, as applied at module install time
CHANGED: Some superficial formatting rules to better match Moodle style checkers
ADDED: Per-instance configuration of avilable mask types and question fields
ADDED: Solution for moving masks from page to page after one uploads a document update with more or less pages than the original

Release 2.7.006
---------------
HOUSEKEEPING: Minor code formatting changes

Release 2.7.005
---------------
FIXED: Issues reported in moodle submission
FIXED: Vulnerability relating to teacher form editing
FIXED: postgresql compatibility issue

Release 2.7.004
---------------
FIXED: An issue that broke installation. The moodle code checkers complain if there are missing save points in the upgrade process - but installation fails if the savepoints are added during installation
FIXED: Module completion problem
FIXED: Module name was displayed as MASKS but official name is MASK
FIXED: texts missing from FR translations
FIXED: Frame size problem on Firefox
FIXED: Jquery 3.0 compatibility (use in Moodle 3.2)
FIXED: z-index of module page
ADDED: new error pop-up before upload if pdf2svg command line is incorrect
FIXED: wrong update of student progression in page header

Release 2.7.003
---------------
FIXED: Incompatibility with Postgresql
FIXED: False error message displayed after uploading the PDF
FIXED: Navigation menu broken display on Moodle 3.2
FIXED: Collision between footer and upload popup with Theme Essential
FIXED: Teacher questions states reset in editing mode
FIXED: coding style in js, php and css files
ADDED: Possibility of shift masks of pages to the right or left page

